text:
@XYIYX: This isn’t just tech it’s about law and human rights. Turning workers into constant data sources to train robots raises serious issues around consent, privacy, and fair pay.
Innovation is fine, but not at the cost of human dignity. Employment laws exist to protect workers, and using people to train systems that may replace them will eventually face legal pushback.
There’s also an economic risk if jobs disappear without transition, it impacts income and GDP. Technology should support humans, not quietly replace them. The real question isn’t “can we do this?” but “should we?” and under what rules.
